                        "displayName": "Abishek Muthian",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
                    },
                    "body": "[~apitrou], sorry for the trouble this might not be a bug and due to user error regarding environmental variables when using sudo to install pyarrow after building.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure why unavailability env vars can cause compiler to detect incorrect CPU capabilities. But, if I use sudo -E to export env vars from the build session this error doesn't occur.\r\n\r\nAlthough there are similar errors such as the one I've posted here on the github, since there's not clear evidence of an error within the project I'll close this as 'Not A Bug'.\r\n\r\nI've written a [gist|https://gist.github.com/heavyinfo/04e1326bb9bed9cecb19c2d603c8d521]\u00a0detailing all the setups needed to build and install arrow, pyarrow in ARM if anyone needed.",
